local scope

Variables created inside a function.
def func():
    x = 10
    print(x)

func()
# print(x) ‚ùå Error: x is not defined outside

Enclosing scope

Variables in a function inside another function.
def outer():
    y = 20
    def inner():
        print(y)
    inner()

outer()

Global scope

Variables declared outside all functions.
z = 30

def show():
    print(z)

show()

    | Scope     | Where defined     | Accessible     |
| --------- | ----------------- | -------------- |
| Local     | Inside function   | Only there     |
| Enclosing | Outer function    | Inner function |
| Global    | Outside functions | Everywhere     |
| Built-in  | Python itself     | Everywhere     |
